<Base title="And Rivers Will Flow with Date Syrup — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>And Rivers Will Flow with Date Syrup</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Galeria Promocyjna | 2023</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Painting series addressing societal discontent through utopian imagination. Grzyma&#322;a explores what an improved world might entail, depicting fantastical scenarios where social hierarchies dissolve. Her work begins with the fairy tale closing "and they lived happily ever after," then visualizes stages toward collective transformation. Features surreal imagery: "The Pope will talk to dolphins, businessmen will sit in school desks." Rather than placing utopia in distant fantasy lands, Grzyma&#322;a locates it specifically in contemporary Poland—among Ursyn&oacute;w's apartment blocks. Includes a radio presentation and visitor participation notebook.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Artist:</strong> Ania Grzyma&#322;a</p>
      <p><strong>Curator:</strong> Michalina Sablik</p>
      <p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Kaja Werbanowska</p>
      <p><strong>Partners:</strong> Academy of Fine Arts in Warsaw, ENTRY Initiative</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
